Benchmark design considerations:
- Cover all performance dimensions students will encounter
- Platform-specific baselines prevent confusion
- Cost-performance tradeoffs made explicit
- Memory usage patterns for resource planning

Key metrics chosen:
- Tokens/second: Industry standard for LLM performance
- Latency percentiles: User experience impact
- Memory allocation: Container sizing requirements
- Cost per operation: Budget planning
- Cache hit rates: Optimization effectiveness

Real-world scenarios:
- Small frequent requests (chatbots)
- Large batch processing (document analysis)
- High concurrency (production APIs)
- Memory accumulation (long-running agents)

Workshop value:
- Students can benchmark their own code
- Compare different strategies quantitatively
- Understand platform limitations before deployment
- Make data-driven architecture decisions
